{"title":"Basil Halperin, observations on academia and research","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/899180750/0/marginalrevolution~Basil-Halperin-observations-on-academia-and-research.html","date":1717917796000,"content":"<blockquote><p>Miscellaneous things I learned in [econ] grad school: 1. The returns to experience are high(er than I thought) – Someone who has studied a single topic for a decade or two or three really does know a LOT about that topic</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>It is worth clicking through to read <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://x.com/BasilHalperin/status/1799138472969826523\" target=\"_blank\">the whole thread</a>.  People should be writing more about how things actually work!  This is oddly grossly undersupplied.  His points about seminars are especially interesting and well-taken.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/basil-halperin-observations-on-academia-and-research.html\">Basil Halperin, observations on academia and research</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/899180750/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/899180750/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/899180750/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/899180750/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/899180750/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://f